Belgium Calls Attack on U.K. Embassy in Iran ‘Unacceptable’

-- B y   A n d r e w   C l a p h a m
-- 
2011-12-01T11:56:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/belgium-calls-attack-on-u-k-embassy-in-iran-unacceptable-.html
Belgium’s Foreign Ministry yesterday
told the Iranian ambassador in Brussels that the attack on the
U.K. embassy in Tehran was “unacceptable,” said Michel Malherbe, a spokesman for the ministry.  Belgium has no intention at the moment to recall its
ambassador to  Iran , Malherbe said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Clapham in Brussels at 
 aclapham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at   acullen8@bloomberg.net  